From Lyra.Silverwolf at students.olin.edu  Sat Nov  2 10:00:57 2013
From: Lyra.Silverwolf at students.olin.edu (Lyra Silverwolf)
Date: Sat, 2 Nov 2013 10:00:57 -0400
Subject: [Carpediem] National Novel Writing Month
Message-ID: <6DFAD39A-86B4-47F9-ACC4-A6F647674033@students.olin.edu>

Hey all,

In case you didn't already know, November is national novel writing month! That means that a bunch of people devote the entire month of November to writing a 50,000 word novel from scratch. A couple of us here at Olin are participating and we even have a mailing list. If you're interested, check out nanowrimo.org and join the mailing list nanowrimo at lists.olin.edu.

-Lyra

Hi All!

This weekend is the beginning of FWOP's largest undertaking yet: Building (=
almost) a 2 storey house! A large part of the building involves assembling =
platforms to build a 2nd storey that's about 30 feet across by 12 feet deep=
. We also have to assemble 4 beds, a dining table etc. etc. etc. It's a mas=
sive undertaking and we need your help!

If you love woodwork, love building houses or both, come help us! Your time=
 commitment can be any subset of Saturday 9th November 12pm - 8pm and Sunda=
y 10th November 12pm - 8pm.

If you'd like to help us, please fill in this google form just so we have a=
 list of how many people we have to help us: https://docs.google.com/forms/=
d/1n094Z3kc6VHAsaioueE7X_QhSCajdxlzsJQ6jD-v7yc/viewform

Please help us! We really need the help if you can afford it!

Cheers,
FWOP

From Aditi.Joshi at students.olin.edu  Sun Nov  3 20:54:43 2013
From: Aditi.Joshi at students.olin.edu (Aditi Joshi)
Date: Sun, 3 Nov 2013 20:54:43 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Diwali Celebration!
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336441EC37@EXVS01.olin.edu>

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336441EC37EXVS01oline_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

TL;DR: Olin's Diwali celebration is going to be on November 9th at 6pm. Sig=
n up here<https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=3D0An4HMnEPu3pddHhWTT=
VQMmVEZmJseWNibDBwY0V0Smc&usp=3Ddrive_web#gid=3D0>, if you want to attend o=
r help!

Long version:
Olin is planning a Diwali celebration for next Saturday! Diwali, for those =
of you who don't know, is the Indian festival of lights. It's always a lot =
of fun, and we want to bring that spirit to Olin! The actual event will be =
the 9th at 6pm but on the Friday before that we are going to be having grou=
ps come together for preparations. We are going to have three different "co=
mmittees" that are going to be working on different things:
-dandiyas (which are going to be used for the dance component that we're go=
ing to have, aka these things<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dandiya_Raas>)
-diyas (lamps that we will light, aka these things<http://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Diya_(light)>)
-food (any combinations of these things<https://www.google.com/search?q=3Di=
ndian+food&source=3Dlnms&tbm=3Disch&sa=3DX&ei=3DBf52UpbdFo-_sQSNq4D4Cg&ved=
=3D0CAkQ_AUoAQ&biw=3D1600&bih=3D799>)
Sign up on this googledoc<https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=3D0An=
4HMnEPu3pddHhWTTVQMmVEZmJseWNibDBwY0V0Smc&usp=3Ddrive_web#gid=3D0> to figur=
e out which one of the things you want to help with or even if you just wan=
t to come!
Also let me know if you have any questions and/or suggestions!

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336441EC37EXVS01oline_

TL;DR: Olin's Diwali celebration is going to be on November 9th at 6pm. Sig=
n up here<https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=3D0An4HMnEPu3pddHhWTT=
VQMmVEZmJseWNibDBwY0V0Smc&usp=3Ddrive_web#gid=3D0>, if you want to attend o=
r help!

Long version:
Olin is planning a Diwali celebration for next Saturday! Diwali, for those =
of you who don't know, is the Indian festival of lights. It's always a lot =
of fun, and we want to bring that spirit to Olin! The actual event will be =
the 9th at 6pm but on the Friday before that we are going to be having grou=
ps come together for preparations. We are going to have three different "co=
mmittees" that are going to be working on different things:
-dandiyas (which are going to be used for the dance component that we're go=
ing to have, aka these things<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dandiya_Raas>)
-diyas (lamps that we will light, aka these things<http://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Diya_(light)>)
-food (any combinations of these things<https://www.google.com/search?q=3Di=
ndian+food&source=3Dlnms&tbm=3Disch&sa=3DX&ei=3DBf52UpbdFo-_sQSNq4D4Cg&ved=
=3D0CAkQ_AUoAQ&biw=3D1600&bih=3D799>)
Sign up on this googledoc<https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=3D0An=
4HMnEPu3pddHhWTTVQMmVEZmJseWNibDBwY0V0Smc&usp=3Ddrive_web#gid=3D0> to figur=
e out which one of the things you want to help with or even if you just wan=
t to come!
Also let me know if you have any questions and/or suggestions!

depending on how quick you are at it. Let us know if you want in.

Meat club will be hosting the second ever Olin College Chili Cook-off! Chil=
i will be served in the dining hall during lunch on Monday, November 11th .

To Compete: All students are eligible to compete by themselves or in teams.=
 Each team will have a budget to spend on ingredients and will turn in thei=
r chili on Sunday night. If you are interested in competing you must regist=
er by emailing Chris or James by 5pm on Thursday. 1st Place by people's cho=
ice and as judged by dining hall staff will each receive a prize! More deta=
ils will be emailed to all competitors on Thursday night.

To Judge: Simply show up to the dining hall next Monday (the 11th) for lunc=
h (noon) and all the chili will be there along with judging cards.

-Meat Club

From Lauren.Froschauer at students.olin.edu  Mon Nov  4 23:14:08 2013
From: Lauren.Froschauer at students.olin.edu (Lauren Froschauer)
Date: Mon, 4 Nov 2013 23:14:08 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Lumen Lantern Survey- Please Help a FBE team w/ 2
 minutes of your time!
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336441F68E@EXVS01.olin.edu>

--_004_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336441F68EEXVS01oline_
Content-Type: multipart/alternative;
	boundary="_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336441F68EEXVS01oline_"

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336441F68EEXVS01oline_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello Everyone!

Our FBE (Entrepreneurial Initiative) team is testing the market viability o=
f our product, Lumen Lanterns (which you may have seen hanging in the WH3 a=
nte lounge). If you could spare a minute of your time to fill out our quick=
 survey, you'd be a great help to our project. Thanks!

Lumen Lanterns are customizable acrylic lanterns intended to be hung in you=
r room to illuminate the space in an interesting and creative way. The side=
s and LED of the lantern can be swapped to change its effect. For example, =
on Halloween you can turn it into a jack o'lantern, while on Hanukkah you c=
an make it into a. We plan to provide sets of holiday and seasonal inserts,=
 although creative minds are free to make original designs as well.

We have two models: Medium (3"x3" base) and Large (4"x4" base). We plan to =
sell them both individually and in a pack of two Medium and one Large.

Please fill out this survey, takes no more than 2 minutes!  https://www.sur=
veymonkey.com/s/3SNVXSL
[cid:image001.jpg at 01CED9B3.8F10A850] (Lumen Lantern with Fall Designs)
Thanks a Bunch!

F.I.L.M. Club Presents: The Sessions<http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DFy2y7=
UIpgP4>
10:00 pm Today, Auditorium

[cid:image003.jpg at 01CEDA1D.50AFD350]

I've been wanting to see this film for a while. Originally titled The Surro=
gate, The Sessions is a 2012 drama based on the article "On Seeing a Sex Su=
rrogate" by Mark O'Brien. John Hawkes portrays O'Brien, a poet paralyzed fr=
om the neck down due to polio.

John Arakaki, F.I.L.M. Director
Amanda Lee, 95 Minute Run Time
Travis Lewis, Prepare for Future Folk
Philicia Chow, Pot stickers

Tl;dr: COME VISIT CAITRIN TO LEARN MORE ABOUT AHS FROM 9-10pm TONIGHT. AC10=
9.

Just wanted to make sure you all saw this message from the AHS Committee.  =
Caitrin is planning on being around to talk to students about their AHS con=
centrations and classes at Olin (etc.).  She'll be around from 9-10PM outsi=
de of AC109 and would love to chat.  I think this is a great opportunity to=
 learn more about the AHS curriculum and I highly recommend getting your qu=
estions answered sooner rather than later.  See below for more information.

Thanks!
Sharon

From: AHS
Sent: Tuesday, November 05, 2013 10:46 PM
To: Students - All Olin Students
Subject: AHS credits and Registration Info!

Hi Olin students,

Welcome to spring 2014 Registration Time! Some info from the Land of AHS:

1. Open Hours: To answer AHS questions, Caitrin Lynch will hold special AHS=
 Office Hours on Wednesday, Nov. 6 from 9-10 pm, in the hallway outside AC =
109.

2. AHS requirements: If you are wondering what AHS requirements you will ne=
ed to fulfill for graduation, check out http://ahs.olin.edu/ , which includ=
es
info about Concentrations, Capstones, and more. A lot of your questions abo=
ut AHS can be answered there, including questions about putting an AHS Foun=
dation
course into a Concentration and doing an AHS Capstone while Away.

3. AHS Capstone & Prepstone: We encourage students to do AHS Capstone in ju=
nior year, if at all possible. But senior year works too. If you plan to do=
 an AHS Capstone, a prerequisite for registering for the project is success=
ful completion of the AHS Capstone Preparatory Workshop (aka Prepstone). Th=
is is an unscheduled activity--you do it on your own time, and have checkin=
s with the prof and Course Assistant. One credit, graded as credit/no credi=
t.Easy but extremely useful and important. Don't forget to register for it!=
 You can do it any semester--it does not need to be the semester immediatel=
y prior to doing the Capstone. If you are not sure if you want to do a Proj=
ect, this is a good exercise to sign up for to give you time to figure it o=
ut. (It is 100% fine if you decide to not to the project after/while doing =
Prepstone.)

4. Sophomores and AHS Concentrations: You will get an email in the spring a=
sking you to declare if you are going the AHS or E! route. If AHS, your AHS=
 Concentration plans will be due in March. We suggest you think about this =
now so you can try to sign up for a Concentration course for the spring.  Y=
our AHS Concentration consists of twelve or more credits of AHS coursework =
that build on each other (usually in the same discipline). The AHS Capstone=
 can be used to satisfy the final four credits of the AHS Concentration. Fo=
r more information please refer to http://ahs.olin.edu/concentration.html  =
.

5. Juniors going the AHS path: If you don't yet have an approved approved C=
oncentration, please contact us to tell us your new plans. This is the time=
 to get your plans straightened out.

6. Sustainability certificate students: Although the SUST courses (the Intr=
o & Synthesis courses) do not earn AHS or E! credit, and therefore one cann=
ot put them into an AHS or E! Concentration, students doing the Sustainabil=
ity certificate program may be able to create a hybrid AHS/E! Concentration=
. If this interests you, contact Caitrin Lynch (for AHS) and Lawrence Neele=
y (for E!). ARB may also provide some relief for students who are doing the=
 certificate program and are having a difficult time completing the require=
d 28 credits of AHSE!. Contact your adviser to discuss this.

Thank you! Caitrin, for the AHS Committee



--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE40133645CF568EXVS01oline_

:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p></div><div><p class=3DMsoNormal><span s=

 <b>AHS requirements</b>: If you are wondering what </span><b><span style=

Calibri","sans-serif";color:black'>you will need to fulfill&nbsp;for gradua=

 which includes<o:p></o:p></span></p></div><div><p class=3DMsoNormal><span =

nfo about Concentrations, Capstones, and more. A lot of your questions abou=

Foundation<o:p></o:p></span></p></div><div><p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=

 into a Concentration and doing an AHS Capstone while Away.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p=
></span></p></div><div><p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:10.5pt=
;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></=
p></div><div><p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:10.5pt;font-fami=
ly:"Calibri","sans-serif";color:black'>3. <b>AHS Capstone &amp; Prepstone</=
b>: We encourage students to do </span><b><span style=3D'font-size:14.0pt;f=
ont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";color:red'>AHS Capstone</span></b><span s=

pan><span style=3D'font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";colo=
r:black'>in junior year, if at all possible. But senior year works too. If =
you plan to&nbsp;do an AHS Capstone, a prerequisite for registering for the=
 project is&nbsp;successful completion of the AHS Capstone Preparatory Work=
shop (aka Prepstone).&nbsp;This is an unscheduled activity--you do it on yo=
ur own time, and have checkins&nbsp;with the prof and Course Assistant. One=
 credit, graded as credit/no credit.Easy but extremely useful and important=
. Don't forget to register for it! You&nbsp;can do it any semester--it does=
 not need to be the semester immediately prior&nbsp;to doing the Capstone. =
If you are not sure if you want to do a Project, this is&nbsp;a good exerci=
se to sign up for to give you time to figure it out. (It is 100%&nbsp;fine =
if you decide to not to the project after/while doing Prepstone.)<o:p></o:p=
></span></p></div><div><p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:10.5pt=
;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></=
p></div><div><p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:10.5pt;font-fami=
ly:"Calibri","sans-serif";color:black'>4. <b>Sophomores and AHS </b></span>=
<b><span style=3D'font-size:14.0pt;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";color=
:red'>Concentrations</span></b><span style=3D'font-size:10.5pt;font-family:=
"Calibri","sans-serif";color:black'>: You will get an email in the spring a=
sking you to&nbsp;declare if you are going the AHS or E! route. If AHS, you=
r AHS Concentration&nbsp;plans will be due in March. We suggest you think a=
bout this now so you can try&nbsp;to sign up for a Concentration course for=
 the spring.&nbsp;&nbsp;Your AHS&nbsp;Concentration consists of twelve or m=
ore credits of AHS coursework that build on each other (usually in the same=
 discipline). The AHS Capstone can be used to satisfy the final four credit=
s of the AHS Concentration. For more information please refer to <a href=3D=
"http://ahs.olin.edu/concentration.html">http://ahs.olin.edu/concentration.=
html</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;.<o:p></o:p></span></p></div><div><p class=3DMsoNormal>=

ack'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p></div><div><p class=3DMsoNormal><span styl=

From wcdolphin at gmail.com  Wed Nov  6 22:16:28 2013
From: wcdolphin at gmail.com (Cory Dolphin)
Date: Wed, 6 Nov 2013 22:16:28 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Work at the number one Twitter in America
Message-ID: <CAOwq=TsBUCc-=3PjMhJGStMS+GsSzsmRiLDJT25EzG89G9JVxQ@mail.gmail.com>

--047d7b5d965710f15f04ea8db163
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1

The short: apply to intern at Twitter
here<https://hire.jobvite.com/CompanyJobs/Careers.aspx?nl=1&k=Job&j=onDqXfw7&s=DIY>
.

The cool:
That's right Twitter is hiring interns, and we want you! (where you is
presumably an Olin student with some amount of desire to write computer
programs). Don't know if you really want to work at Twitter, check out
these reviews from former interns:

"I ate a lot of food, and it was all delicious. Come for programming, stay
for lunch, and dinner, and unlimited snacks" -David Gaynor

"Twitter? Never heard of it." -Paul Booth

"Sorry, what was that?, I was using the product I built" - Reyner Crosby

"The projects were really interesting, the people were really nice, and I
learned a ton" -Matt Belland

"So good, you'll never want to go back to school" -Noah Tye

If these reviews aren't enough to get you pumped to work at Twitter, then
remember that while interning you will be able to:

- Work on projects impacting millions of users
- Solve hard problems. And probably some really hard problems.
- Take free Get paid to take classes in Android, IOS, Scala and much more
- Have your own gym, your own showers and your own three meals a day

Don't know if you got the skills? Have you a) been programming for over a
year, and/or taken OlinJS or MobDev? If so, apply!
Otherwise, you might want a bit more experience, but apply next year!

If you missed the apply link at the top of the email here it is
again<https://hire.jobvite.com/CompanyJobs/Careers.aspx?nl=1&k=Job&j=onDqXfw7&s=DIY>.
If you have any questions and/or complaints please feel free to email me!

Thanks,
Cory

--047d7b5d965710f15f04ea8db163

 welcome-consider it a (lame) gift from CORe.

te it back to the EH Kitchen since it's free for you to take).


Either way please take it from me. Otherwise it's being thrown out.


Brian

TL;DR FREE BROKEN ICE MACHINE


Hey Guys!

So CORe bought us an ice maker last year. Somehow over the summer it broke =
/ was broken.. which is sadness.

Anyway I've been attempting CPR to revive it but all my attempts have been =
unsuccessful.


If you would like to take this broken ice machine from me you are more than=
 welcome-consider it a (lame) gift from CORe.
(Plus if you get it working again you get to keep it! /Or... you could dona=
te it back to the EH Kitchen since it's free for you to take).


Either way please take it from me. Otherwise it's being thrown out.


Brian

Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

Relationships. We all have them, whether with a romantic partner, with your=
 family, or with anyone else you interact with regularly. What makes a good=
 relationship, what makes a bad relationship, and how can we be more intent=
ional about making our relationships awesome?

Bring your own dinner. We'll bring the desserts. Desserts not made in the d=
ining hall.
Tuesday, November 12th 6-7:30 pm in the Crescent Room. iCal attached.

Led by Amos Meeks '14, who will be giving this talk as part of MIT's Splash=
 program in a few weeks.

[cid:image002.jpg at 01CEDA71.BB4B7FD0]

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336474CD73EXVS01oline_

From Henry.Horsey at students.olin.edu  Thu Nov  7 21:10:17 2013
From: Henry.Horsey at students.olin.edu (Henry Horsey)
Date: Thu, 7 Nov 2013 21:10:17 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Drive on Saturday to Advance the Cause of America
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336474CF1A@EXVS01.olin.edu>

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336474CF1AEXVS01oline_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

Hey ya'll,

This Saturday, a subset of EH 2N, colloquially referred to in the present v=
ernacular as 'Them Awesome Flag-Wavin' Bald-Eagle Savin' Patriot Fellers,' =
need a set of individuals to drive from our humble patriotic abode to the w=
ilds of the Lulu to help rescue Wellesley students trapped in the confines =
of a pinko commie  communal commune thingy. Several hours after these stude=
nts have been rescued, they will need transportation back to their abode, a=
fter having been converted to the cause of America. The pay per hour for dr=
iving a shift into this uncharted territory is $10, with an extra $5 added =
for those who can supply their own wheels. The rescue mission shift will ru=
n from 10:00 to 12:00, with a return shift from 1:00 to 3:00.

Be a patriot, be an American: Sign up today.

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336474CF1AEXVS01oline_

Hello students,

Lauren Taaffe works in the Development Office at Olin, and she is in need o=
f a babysitting during Wednesday, Nov. 13. Her email is below:

"I have to make a trip out of town next Wednesday, Nov 13, with Lynn Stein,=
 and I am now in urgent need of a babysitter for my 12 year old daughter ne=
xt Wednesday evening. I need someone to be at home with her from as early a=
s 3 pm through about 9:30 or 10 pm, although the person could possibly come=
 over at 5 or 5:30 if that was the earliest they could start. We live in Ne=
wton, just about 20 minutes from campus. It's an easy job: dinner, homework=
, play a game or two. It's not really babysitting, since she is not a baby,=
 she just isn't able to be at home alone in the evening yet."

Please contact her at Lauren.Taaffe at olin.edu<mailto:Lauren.Taaffe at olin.edu>=
 if you are interested!

Best,

Geeta Gubba

geeta at students.olin.edu<mailto:geeta at students.olin.edu>

al design. This is a great opportunity for MEs and BioEs. This event is a c=
ollaboration between Harvard, Boston University, Olin College, Tufts Univer=
sity, and MIT. Engineering students from these five institutions are invite=
d to attend. Registration is required as attendance is capped for each part=
icipating university. Please RSVP to Suzanne.<mailto:suzanne.alcott at olin.ed=
u>  Transportation will be provided. For a complete list of companies, clic=

Ya'll,

This is a critical mater to the state of the nation: either you are a drive=
r, or you are not a driver. If you are not a driver, you are not a patriot.=
 Patriots are good, not patriots are not good. Be a patriot. Be a driver.

Uncle Sam is calling. Pick up the phone.


From: Henry Horsey
Sent: Thursday, November 07, 2013 9:10 PM
To: carpediem at lists.olin.edu; helpme at lists.olin.edu
Subject: Drive on Saturday to Advance the Cause of America

Hey ya'll,

This Saturday, a subset of EH 2N, colloquially referred to in the present v=
ernacular as 'Them Awesome Flag-Wavin' Bald-Eagle Savin' Patriot Fellers,' =
need a set of individuals to drive from our humble patriotic abode to the w=
ilds of the Lulu to help rescue Wellesley students trapped in the confines =
of a pinko commie  communal commune thingy. Several hours after these stude=
nts have been rescued, they will need transportation back to their abode, a=
fter having been converted to the cause of America. The pay per hour for dr=
iving a shift into this uncharted territory is $10, with an extra $5 added =
for those who can supply their own wheels. The rescue mission shift will ru=
n from 10:00 to 12:00, with a return shift from 1:00 to 3:00.

Be a patriot, be an American: Sign up today.

From Logan.Davis at students.olin.edu  Sat Nov  9 12:55:07 2013
From: Logan.Davis at students.olin.edu (Logan Davis)
Date: Sat, 9 Nov 2013 12:55:07 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] FWOP Set Build All Day Today
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE40133648673CE@EXVS01.olin.edu>

tl;dr Come help FWOP build, paint, and interior decorate a house. Noon to 11PM today, noon to 10PM tomorrow. Free pizza and undying gratitude for volunteers. 

Hello Oliners!

This Thursday, Friday, and Saturday, the Franklin W. Olin Players will be presenting our fall play, Brighton Beach Memoirs. It?s a hilarious comedy! It?s a heart-wrenching drama! It has an incredibly complicated set! We need your help!

The set for Brighton Beach Memoirs is a two-story house, complete with living room, dining room, bedrooms, stairs, tables, couches, benches, and chairs? and we?re building it right now. Ever wanted to get experience with house-painting? With platform-building? Then come to Sorenson Theater any time between now and 11PM today, and any time between noon and 10 PM tomorrow. We will reward you with our undying gratitude. And love. And free pizza for dinner. And lots of paint splotches on your shirt. 

Thanks!
-Logan Davis
(and FWOP)

       *Updates from the Foundry
<http://olincollege.createsend1.com/t/d-l-mtjhuk-l-d/>*

Boston Startup Weekend<http://olincollege.createsend1.com/t/d-l-mtjhuk-l-n/>
 <http://olincollege.createsend1.com/t/d-l-mtjhuk-l-p/>

Startup Weekend <http://olincollege.createsend1.com/t/d-l-mtjhuk-l-x/> is
coming to Boston on November 15th at Boston University. Hang out with
Boston's best and brightest entrepreneurs for a weekend-long startup
hackathon!  Bring your ideas and leadership skills.  Registration is $50 -
sign yourself up at
Eventbrite<http://olincollege.createsend1.com/t/d-l-mtjhuk-l-m/>.
 Shoot an to email to foundry at lists.olin.edu and we'll help you coordinate
rides.

The Foundry

The Foundry is a student run organization that works to foster and promote
entrepreneurship at Olin. We'll soon start sending out regular emails about
startup-related events in the Boston area.  If you'd like to get the word
out about an upcoming event, drop us a line at info at olinfoundry.org with
suggestions! Also, please let us know what types of events you'd be
interested in hearing about.

From William.Saulnier at students.olin.edu  Sun Nov 10 16:00:14 2013
From: William.Saulnier at students.olin.edu (William Saulnier)
Date: Sun, 10 Nov 2013 16:00:14 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Olin Wii Sports Ladder Competition: Season 0 Starts
	TODAY
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401336375041F@EXVS01.olin.edu>

Hello everyone!

I would like to announce the first ever campus-wide Olin Wii Sports Ladder Competition!

This competition will be a battle to discover who is the best at Wii Sports Tennis (and other sports as I implement them!). There will be a trophy at the end!

Why is it Season 0? Because we're starting in the middle of the semester and a lot of the formula and rules are subject to change based on factors that come up as we playtest.

The rules are:

0. Matches are to be played on Wii Sports Club for the Wii U or on Wii Sports Resort Tennis for Wii. The original Wii Sports is not supported.
1. If you are challenged by another player, you must play them. No harassing people with challenges. You can of course play for fun, but the only matches you can report are when you challenge or have been challeneged.
2. Tennis matches are best of 3 (first to 2 games)
3. One person reports the match and the score at the end on the website.

Sign up here: http://wiisports.enigmasm.com/
And start playing! I hope you enjoy.

Subject: [Carpediem] [MSFT] Make an app, get a free smartphone

Microsoft and Nokia are holding a mini-hackathon in Boston next Saturday to=
 teach people how to create and publish apps for the Windows Phone platform=
. Since everybody likes freebies, I thought I'd mention that if you publish=
 an app (no matter how basic, but needs to pass validation) within two week=
s after the event, you will get a Nokia Lumia 620.

Participation is free, but seats are limited and almost filled up. Therefor=
e, please don't sign up if you're not 100% going.


1)      You need a DVLUP account to register (create one for free at http:/=
/www.dvlup.com)

2)      Register with your DVLUP username at https://nokiadvlupdayboston.ev=
entbrite.com/

3)      Fill in your name to organize transport. Google spreadsheet<https:/=
/docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=3D0Aj88csM5JaDadDNPazdxaUJhS2ZqRHlROFR=
NbDVyR0E&usp=3Dsharing>

If you are interested but unavailable Saturday, fill in the Google spreadsh=
eet<https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=3D0Aj88csM5JaDadDNPazdxaUJh=
S2ZqRHlROFRNbDVyR0E&usp=3Dsharing> anyway. If there are enough people, I'll=
 probably be able to convince my contact to give an app lab at Olin complet=
e with Nokia swag and phones. Just sayin'.

--Steven

>  <http://olincollege.createsend1.com/t/d-l-mtjhuk-l-p/>
>
> Startup Weekend <http://olincollege.createsend1.com/t/d-l-mtjhuk-l-x/> is
> coming to Boston on November 15th at Boston University. Hang out with
> Boston's best and brightest entrepreneurs for a weekend-long startup
> hackathon!  Bring your ideas and leadership skills.  Registration is $50 -
> sign yourself up at Eventbrite<http://olincollege.createsend1.com/t/d-l-mtjhuk-l-m/>.
>  Shoot an to email to foundry at lists.olin.edu and we'll help you
> coordinate rides.
>
> The Foundry
>
> The Foundry is a student run organization that works to foster and promote
> entrepreneurship at Olin. We'll soon start sending out regular emails about
> startup-related events in the Boston area.  If you'd like to get the word
> out about an upcoming event, drop us a line at info at olinfoundry.org with
> suggestions! Also, please let us know what types of events you'd be
> interested in hearing about.
>
>
>

Bio Med Night at Olin College
Tuesday, November 12th 7-9 PM AC 113

of 2006,  will then introduce Oliners to life at Stryker, a leading medical=

heir jobs more efficiently. Coffee and cookies will be served. Please email=

Bio Med Night at Olin College
Tonight 7-9 PM AC 113
The bio med night will kick off at 7PM with Alumna Amanda Blackwood discuss=
ing the BioMedical Engineering program at WPI. Amanda is currently pursuing=
 a PhD in this program. At 8PM Dr. Polina Segalova, Olin partner and class =
of 2006,  will then introduce Oliners to life at Stryker, a leading medical=
 technology company dedicated to helping healthcare professionals perform t=
heir jobs more efficiently. Coffee and cookies will be served. Please email=
 Suzanne<mailto:suzanne.alcott at olin.edu> if you plan to attend.


Suzanne Alcott
Corporate Relations Coordinator
781-292-2282 (p)

Hi,

--------
There will be a screening of the recently released film, "Inequality for Al=
l", in Collins Cinema on Nov. 14 at 7 pm.  The film discusses an important =
issue facing the U.S. and I hope you will be able to attend.  More informat=
ion about the film follows:

You can view the official trailer here:  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3D9=
REdcxfie3M

More about the film is available at its website: http://inequalityforall.co=
m/

And a review: http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/inequality-for-all-2013

From Michael.Warner at students.olin.edu  Tue Nov 12 15:55:52 2013
From: Michael.Warner at students.olin.edu (Michael Warner)
Date: Tue, 12 Nov 2013 15:55:52 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] I want to pie you in the face
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE4013363E0A51B@EXVS01.olin.edu>

--_002_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE4013363E0A51BEXVS01oline_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

Brave charitable people of Olin!

I am submitting a SERV auction item that will grant the winner the ability =
to choose someone for me to pie in the face. However, I need a list of will=
ing participants from which the auctioneers can choose a victim. Be a champ=
 and sign up by emailing me. Or get your friends to instead. At the moment,=
 I have thirty or so names, but the more the merrier.=20

Pieing will be painless, performed away from electronic equipment, and, if =
you so wish, I will get your clothes washed for you (pie will consist solel=
y of whip cream). However, no guarantees that it won't be embarrassing.  In=
 fact, embarrassment will be maximized in dramatic fashion (probably involv=
ing me in tights).

Don't be a bitch, do it for charity.=20

Love,
Schmitty

PS: If you have specific conditions during which you don't want to get pied=
, let me know. For example, Diana doesn't want me to pie her when her hair =
isn't tied back. Whatever.

PPS: I realize the inherent hypocrisy of pressuring you to sign up to get p=
ied when I cannot myself be on the list. Trust me though, whatever I choose=
 to wear during this event will be the most embarrassing thing about this.


--_002_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE4013363E0A51BEXVS01oline_

Hey everyone,

Baja will be having short (1/2 hour) design reviews next week before we lea=
ve for Thanksgiving break. We would love to get your feedback on our design=
s. On Monday the 18th, we will be presenting our suspension and electrical =
subsystems. On Thursday the 21st, we will be presenting our drivetrain and =
chassis subsystems. Both presentations will happen during the lunch hour (1=
2:30-1:30).

We are hoping to get feedback on all systems but if you can only make one o=
f the days, please come on Thursday! ICals for both days are attached.

Best,
Kate

From larissa.little at students.olin.edu  Tue Nov 12 17:28:37 2013
From: larissa.little at students.olin.edu (Larissa Little)
Date: Tue, 12 Nov 2013 17:28:37 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Engineering Video Competition - $25,000 Prize
Message-ID: <CAK_k8jqDuhsh22GryoASPLmfCQaFZT9qvi0PHnJbJrzOp4dQJg@mail.gmail.com>

--001a11c3704407601904eb02611f
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1

Found about about this through Vin, here's the info!

[image: E4U Video Contest]



In celebration of its upcoming 50th anniversary, the National Academy of
Engineering is launching Engineering for You (E4U), a video contest to show
the impact that engineering has or will have on society. We are offering a
$25,000 prize to the most inspiring 1-2 minute video focused anywhere
between 1964 and 2064. The contest will run from Nov. 1, 2013, to March 31,
2014.

Learn more at www.e4uvideocontest.org.

 You are invited to join us in highlighting engineering achievements past,
present, and future as well as make others aware of how the engineering
endeavor has benefited humankind. This contest would make a great class
assignment or enhance a capstone project or paper that students are already
working on. In addition, the resulting video could easily end up being
useful to your own institution for recruiting members and presenting the
goals of your organization.

We hope that you will participate in the contest and also encourage those
in your local communities to participate!

Please consider sharing with your:

   - Students
   - Society email Listservs
   - Colleagues
   - Other affiliated organizations/universities
   - On your website

For any additional questions, please email
E4Uvideocontest at nae.edu<http://www.nae.edu/e4u/E4Uvideocontest at nae.edu>
.

--001a11c3704407601904eb02611f

Hello carpe!

For the past year and a half I've been working for a woman in Needham on we=
ekends (generally every other Saturday or so, from 10am to 3pm on the long =
days) doing things like painting, raking, gardening, and snow shoveling. I =
usually went with a three other people, but they've all graduated. Would yo=
u like to join me this weekend and for future weekends next semester?

She pays $12 an hour and feeds us [delicious] lunch, so if we work 10am to =
3pm she pays $60 (and we take 45 minutes or so for lunch!)

Let me know if you're interested,
Jackie

From benjamin.kroop at students.olin.edu  Wed Nov 13 00:17:19 2013
From: benjamin.kroop at students.olin.edu (Ben Kroop)
Date: Wed, 13 Nov 2013 00:17:19 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] MIT Flying Club Fly Out to the New England Air Museum
Message-ID: <CAJiEShgyBaX1zeoa3eZLeFhMhCw6tHuKyxEXRpmA7OL-3XA_LA@mail.gmail.com>

--001a11c3844c4c1bb804eb0814c9
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1

Hey Everyone!

The MIT Flying Club is having an event this Sunday. We have eight planes
and we'll be flying them all to Bradley International Airport in CT for the
day to visit the New England Air Museum.

If you want to come fly around in a small plane, or if you want to visit a
cool museum, there's a link to sign up for the event at the bottom of the
email. Because everyone on the trip will be sharing the cost of the planes,
the cost for each passenger is around $70 - $120 (more details below).

*Here's the full description:*

This Sunday we'll be flying to the New England Air Museum at Bradley
International Airport in Windsor Locks, CT. The NEAM has a large collection
of historical aircraft, and exhibits including a history of Sikorsky
Aircraft and the 58th Bombardment Wing Memorial's B-29.

The flight to Bradley is only 70 miles each way, so the total flight time
will be around 1.5 hours.

Please fill out the survey below if you'd like to attend the flyout as a
passenger.

*Cost logistics:*

Each passenger and pilot will pay their share of the cost of renting the
aircraft. The planes are rented by the hour, and the flight time will be
between 1.5 and 2 hours. This brings the total cost per passenger to
between $70 and $120, depending on the plane, number of passengers, and the
weather. Admission to the museum is $12 per person.

Your pilot will be able to provide a more accurate estimate of the trip's
total cost once you are assigned to a plane.

*If you would like to come as a passenger, please fill out this survey as
soon as you can:*

http://goo.gl/j4ALRF

Please let me know if you have any questions.

Thanks,
Ben

--001a11c3844c4c1bb804eb0814c9

From Kennedy.Berry at students.olin.edu  Fri Nov 15 17:22:06 2013
From: Kennedy.Berry at students.olin.edu (Kennedy Berry)
Date: Fri, 15 Nov 2013 17:22:06 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Another Free ticket to see youth symphony concert in
	Boston
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401351B14AF64@EXVS01.olin.edu>

I can't make it, either. If you'd like to go in my stead, let me know ASAP. They're leaving for this at 6 PM.

-Ken

Here's the info on the concert:

Boston Philharmonic Youth Orchestra
VERDI / OVERTURE TO LA FORZA DEL DESTINO
GANDOLFI / THE ZEROROOM AND SOLITON WAVES FROM THE GARDEN OF COSMIC SPECULATION
RAVEL / PIANO CONCERTO IN G
Christopher O'Riley, piano
SHOSTAKOVICH / SYMPHONY NO. 5

Fri, 11/15/2013 - 8:00pm

The first concert of the season for the Boston Philharmonic Youth Orchestra is a m?lange of styles from four different countries, each as different from the other as could be. It's a rich feast for the players in the orchestra, and for the audience too! To start off there is Verdi's Overture to to La forza del destino, a work that is as bracing, dynamic and full of unexpected developments as the opera that follows it. Then a couple of movements from the wondrously varied and beautiful The Garden of Cosmic Speculation, a fascinating, on-going project by the distinguished Boston-based composer Michael Gandolfi.

The first half of the concert closes with the appearance of the much loved pianist Christopher O'Riley, whose hosting of the popular show From the Top has made his name known to just about everybody in America with an interest in classical music. Mr. O'Riley's pianistic credentials are very formidable indeed - he excels as a performer of the some of the most difficult music in the repertory - and he has a special affinity for the subtle and refined music of Ravel, the Piano Concerto in particular. And the concerto's ravishing orchestration makes it a perfect fit for the Youth Philharmonic - with its myriad solos for so many instruments the piece is almost like a concerto for orchestra. 

The second half of the concert is devoted to Shostakovich's great Fifth Symphony. It is an enormous work - not so much in its length as in its emotional reach. It was the piece that placed Shostakovich front and center on the world's musical stage, proclaimed him as the foremost composer of the Soviet Union in the 1930s, and, by giving the illusion of placating the authorities, probably saved his life. Since then, it has come to be regarded as music's greatest symbol of the power of the artist to raise his voice in protest in even the darkest of times.

-----Original Message-----

f the days, please come on Thursday! ICals for both days are attached.

From Alexander.Crease at students.olin.edu  Mon Nov 18 17:42:19 2013
From: Alexander.Crease at students.olin.edu (Alexander Crease)
Date: Mon, 18 Nov 2013 17:42:19 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] The Rules Regarding My Puns
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401351B14BE39@EXVS01.olin.edu>

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401351B14BE39EXVS01oline_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

TLDR: I can't make puns until March 25th, I CAN make puns during winter bre=
ak, and I can make puns during private conversations.

The following message is a PSA regarding the usage of puns by none other th=
an me.

Due to the immense amount of money that was donated to my auction item, I w=
ill no longer be making puns for three months.

After talking with some of the main contributors, some rules and regulation=
s have been laid out, and I just want to make everyone aware of them:

-The definition of a pun for the purposes of this case is "A joke exploitin=
g the fact that there are words that sound alike but have different meaning=
s". THIS DOES NOT INCLUDE WORD-PLAY. Which, as defined for this case, is "v=
erbal wit based on the meanings and ambiguities of words"
-I am allowed to make puns between 3:30PM on 12/19/2013 and 8:00AM on 1/20/=
2013, corresponding to our winter break.
-I am allowed to write all the puns that I think of down, as they will all =
be read aloud once my hiatus has ended.
-I am allowed to make puns in exclusive, private conversations in which I o=
btain consent from whomever I am talking to and there is no chance of anybo=
dy else hearing. This is applicable in a room or group of students as long =
as I obtain consent from every person that could possibly hear me.
-I can trick people into making puns without saying the actual pun myself.

Also, I'm very glad that we were able to raise so much money for SERV. Than=
ks to everybody who contributed.


--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401351B14BE39EXVS01oline_

This Saturday, November 23rd, marks a truly epic day in the history of scie=
nce fiction television. Fifty years ago, a phenomenon was born. A show that=
 shaped science fiction as we know it today. Although it has been fifty yea=
rs, one man has traveled through millennia of time and space, running acros=
s galaxies, turning armies around with just the mention of his name. This m=
an is fire, and ice, and rage. He is the night, and the storm, and the hear=
t of the sun. We all know him as the Doctor. But there is still one questio=
n that has never been answered. The most important question in the universe=
.

DOCTOR WHO?

Come find out as we watch The Day of The Doctor, the 50th Anniversary speci=
al of Doctor Who in the auditorium from 8-10PM this Saturday, November 23rd=
. Food and festivities and general wibbly-wobbly timey-wimey stuff will con=
tinue throughout the night.
There will be games, trivia, a costume contest, and more!
An iCal is attached!
[cid:image003.jpg at 01CEE5E8.94DA7040]

From Jasper.Chen at students.olin.edu  Thu Nov 21 03:03:27 2013
From: Jasper.Chen at students.olin.edu (Jasper Chen)
Date: Thu, 21 Nov 2013 03:03:27 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Boston airport limo groupon
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401351AAB0DF1@EXVS01.olin.edu>

If you happen to get a group of 6 people and the SAC shuttles don't run, then you should consider getting a Boston North Limo Groupon. For $89, you can get a one way trip to the airport, and that's $15 per person. Or for $59, you can get a one way for 3 adults.

- Jasper

ot want to put them in some desolate corner of the internet.

h pictures.

tory channel! But I want to get them out there, make more than just words o=
n a computer.

From Alyssa.Bawgus at students.olin.edu  Thu Nov 21 21:09:08 2013
From: Alyssa.Bawgus at students.olin.edu (Alyssa Bawgus)
Date: Thu, 21 Nov 2013 21:09:08 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] The BedDesk
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401351AF95EA6@EXVS01.olin.edu>

Hello!

You might recognize us from the Dining Hall today, we're the creators of the BedDesk!

We've created a desk attachment for your bed here at Olin that's comfortable and practical for working in bed, skyping, watching movies, and storing your important items next to you through the night. 

If you're interested in purchasing a BedDesk, go to our website www.tinyurl.com/beddesk and click the 'Buy a BedDesk' tab.

If you want to see what the BedDesk is all about risk-free, consider trying one out for the night! With our One Night Night-Stand program, you can rent a BedDesk for 24-hours, and we'll come to you and set you up with a BedDesk to test out.

Thank you for supporting and participating in the 2013 FiBE class! Feel free to ask us any questions by email or in person!

-The BedDeskers

  Greeting Past Moody=92s Mega Math Challenge Participants:



If you enjoyed your experiences with mathematical modeling in a team
environment while in high school, consider participation in another
modeling contest, this one focused on undergraduates.  Participate in this
year's Mathematical Contest in Modeling (MCM).  Last year this contest had
over 6700 college teams from over 25 countries.  This is the most
established and well known undergraduate modeling contest in the world. As
you continue your mathematics education, or studies and careers in any
field in which math forms a strong base of knowledge, you will find your
modeling skills to be valuable. Please see www.mathmodelingcontest.com for
details and join us February 6-10. Registration is open now and remains
open until February 5, 2014.

 kitchen fridge, but I'm away for break. If you want a couple delicious (in=
 my humble opinion) cookies, you should use it! They cook for 9-11 minutes =
at 375. It's in a glass bowl with a green lid. Enjoy!

Cecelia

want to join!

to join in (or help some Oliners out), transportation to Eliot would be muc=
h appreciated!! (We also won't have to get up so early then.)

For the past two years, Dover, DE has held a music festival called FireFly.=
  I went last year and it was insane.  They set up four stages and around 7=
0 bands played over the course of 3 days.  This year, they have extended th=
e festival from 3 to 4 days, added three new stages, and invited over 100 b=
ands.

On December 2nd, they will be selling tickets on sale for CyberMonday.  You=
 can check out past years  at http://fireflyfestival.com/.

I'm already planning on going again but I just wanted to let everyone know =
about the festival.

Jacob

Hello people of carpe,

TLDR: You have too many toiletries from hotels, the homeless have none. I c=
an solve this process by distributing them from you to the needy and make e=
veryone happier.

The long: I run a non-profit which gives toiletries to the homeless, and it=
 really helps if you bring back the toiletries they give you at hotels. The=
y don't use them again, so I am recycling them by giving them to people who=
 need them most. Even one bottle is a great help. I can use shampoo, condit=
ioner, soap, lotion, really anything they give you. If you bring it to Olin=
 I will come and pick it up (and I might even bring you chocolate, you neve=
r know).

Thanks in advance,
Amanda

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401351A952169EXVS01oline_

TLDR: You have too many toiletries from hotels, the homeless have none. I c=
an solve this process by distributing them from you to the needy and make e=
veryone happier.

The long: I run a non-profit which gives toiletries to the homeless, and it=
 really helps if you bring back the toiletries they give you at hotels. The=
y don't use them again, so I am recycling them by giving them to people who=
 need them most. Even one bottle is a great help. I can use shampoo, condit=
ioner, soap, lotion, really anything they give you. If you bring it to Olin=
 I will come and pick it up (and I might even bring you chocolate, you neve=
r know).

Thanks in advance,
Amanda
